{"WIPE":[{"def":"To rub with something soft for cleaning; to clean or dry by rubbing; as, to wipe the hands or face with a towel.","pos":""},{"def":"To remove by rubbing; to rub off; to obliterate; -- usually followed by away, off or out.","pos":""}],"WIPER":[{"def":"A piece generally projecting from a rotating or swinging piece, as an axle or rock shaft, for the purpose of raising stampers, lifting rods, or the like, and leaving them to fall by their own weight; a kind of cam.","pos":""},{"def":"A rod, or an attachment for a rod, for holding a rag with which to wipe out the bore of the barrel.","pos":""}]}